channel.title: Most Wanted Terrorist in Jordan and Iraq Dead
channel.description:
I'm surprised, this is the biggest thing to hit U.S and the world since the arrest of Saddam and no one posted.
Well anyways one of the prime leaders of Al-Queda was tracked and targeted by Special Task force 145. They flew over his safe house in a pair of F-16's and dropped 2 500-Pounder JDAMS right on his bloody house. Dead a little while after they recovered his body.
Story here:
http://www.cnn.com/2006/WORLD/meast/06/08/iraq.al.zarqawi/index.html

The leader of “Al-Qaeda in Iraq” died. I don’t give a damn.

Maybe if it was the leader of “Al-Qaeda in America” this would be important news. But no, we have to go and kill the leader of “Al-Qaeda in Iraq”. Who gives a damn?

There’s thousands of other jihadists saying “Hell yes, now I have chance to be number one!”. Killing one terrorist won’t make a difference, no matter how much the media hypes it up.
